    </fr:authors>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\phi : [0,T] \to  \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> is of <fr:strong>finite variation</fr:strong> if 
<fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ || \phi  ||_{TV([0,T])} = \sup  \left \{ \right \} ]]></fr:tex>
is finite</fr:p>
    <fr:p>where the LHS is the <fr:link type="external" href="total%20variation">total variation</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[[0,T]]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
    <fr:p>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Phi ]]></fr:tex> is of finite variation and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> is a continuous function, we can define the integral <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\int _0^T {f d\phi }]]></fr:tex> as a <fr:link type="external" href="Lebesgue-Stjeltes%20integral">Lebesgue-Stjeltes integral</fr:link></fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
